Before you wire it together you’ll want to see how it will appear. Start by placing one spring on a flat surface, large spring facing downward (on the surface). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Next to the first spring, place another spring, this time with the small spring on the surface and the large spring at the top. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/87/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/87/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Continue this as a pattern while creating a circular shape. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut two to three pieces of wire to bind the springs to one another. Wind one wire to join the top springs and one to join the bottom springs. Considering doubling up if the springs are made from a heavy material or if they aren’t holding together with just one on each side. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Continue winding the wire around the springs to join them together. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7b/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7b/Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Create-a-Vintage-Bedspring-Wreath-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
